text: South Dakota Dept. of Transportation Bridge No. 16-570-054 in rural Corson County, South Dakota was listed on the National Register of Historic Places in 1993. It brings a local road over Oak Creek near McLaughlin, South Dakota. It is a small rural bridge in Corson County, South Dakota. It is a pony truss bridge with king post trusses built by Western Bridge & Construction Co. in 1911.
